            "answer_text": "Intuitively, it's a ruler for abstract sets and you're allowed to break that ruler up into countably many pieces to do the measuring on those countably many subsets that are easily measured.  In normal euclidean space, those easy to measure subsets are intervals or hypercubes, and the measure would be more or less Lebesgue. ",
